# Railway Environment Variables Setup Guide

# Copy these variables to your Railway project's Variables tab
# DO NOT commit actual credentials to Git

# ============================================
# REQUIRED: Zoho OAuth Credentials
# ============================================
# Get these from: https://api-console.zoho.in/
ZOHO_CLIENT_ID=1000.XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
ZOHO_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
ZOHO_REFRESH_TOKEN=1000.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ============================================
# REQUIRED: Employee Identification
# ============================================
# Your employee record ID in Zoho People
EMPLOYEE_ID=1234567890000000000

# Your company email address
EMPLOYEE_EMAIL=yourname@company.com

# Employee API ID (usually same as EMPLOYEE_ID)
EMPLOYEE_API_ID=1234567890000000000

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL: Mapper ID
# ============================================
# Only needed if your organization uses mapper IDs
# MAPPER_ID=

# ============================================
# RAILWAY PLATFORM (Auto-set by Railway)
# ============================================
# PORT is automatically set by Railway
# You don't need to add this variable manually
# PORT=3000

# ============================================
# HOW TO GET YOUR CREDENTIALS
# ============================================

# 1. ZOHO CLIENT_ID & CLIENT_SECRET:
#    - Go to https://api-console.zoho.in/
#    - Create a new "Self Client" application
#    - Copy the Client ID and Client Secret

# 2. ZOHO REFRESH_TOKEN:
#    - Use the OAuth flow to generate a refresh token
#    - Scope required: ZohoPeople.attendance.ALL
#    - See: https://www.zoho.com/accounts/protocol/oauth/web-server-applications.html

# 3. EMPLOYEE_ID & EMPLOYEE_EMAIL:
#    - Your employee ID from Zoho People
#    - Your registered email in Zoho People

# 4. EMPLOYEE_API_ID:
#    - Usually the same as EMPLOYEE_ID
#    - Check the API response to verify the correct ID

